  "known_ambiguities": [
    "The clean source separates request numbers, battle progress, explicit data tags, and ordered command storage, but it does not define this project's canonical byte order, immutable copy contract, typed failure truth table, or SHA-256 envelope.",
    "The source queue implementation file is dirty and is not evidence; only the clean queue header supports the FIFO interface shape, while command sequence numbers begin at one by reviewed project decision.",
    "No sealed source test directly covers empty batches, sequence gaps, duplicate or stale replies, copy alias rejection, canonical hashes, or BattleStepResult field combinations; P1 uses wholly synthetic adversarial and golden vectors for those contracts.",
    "P1 provides fail-closed polymorphic payload, request, and command bases only. P8 owns concrete player decision request and payload variants, while P16 owns concrete state, message, control, and presentation command payloads and their codec.",
    "BattleStepResult reserves the BATTLE_ENDED discriminator but cannot expose a valid ended factory until the P1 outcome contract is available in the following session slice."
